<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01837</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT DEFINING AND CLASSIFYING EMPLOYMENT RELATIONSHIP AMENDING FOR THIS PURPOSE ARTICLES 279, 280 AND 281 OF PRESIDENTIAL DEGREE NO. 442, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINE, AS AMENDED</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to end “endo”, or the practice of “5-5-5’ or “6-6-6” end-of-contract work arrangements-a form of abusive ‘contractualization’ thereby strengthen the right of security of tenure by providing that all employees, irrespective of employment status or position, shall not be dismissed without cause and due process.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>HERRERA-DY, BERNADETTE &quot;BH&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-07-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Welfare</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Romero (023 2016-09-19)</td><td>2. Montoro (025 2016-09-21)</td><tr><td>3. Atienza (025 2016-09-21)</td><td>4. Marcoleta (028 2016-09-28)</td><tr><td>5. Canama (032 2016-10-04)</td><td>6. Alonte (044 2016-11-15)</td><tr><td>7. Aggabao (053 2016-12-07)</td><td>8. Angara-Castillo (062 2017-01-25)</td><tr><td>9. Ty (066 2017-02-06)</td><td>10. Yu (072 2017-02-20)</td><tr><td>11. Bertiz (084 2017-05-02)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06908</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2016-08-02</td></tr></table>